WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.958
Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org

00:10.000 --> 00:12.958
[dramatic music playing]

00:15.083 --> 00:16.000
[coughs]

00:16.000 --> 00:18.083
[Ghoul] <i>Ain't much stays clean
up here, Vaultie.</i>

00:18.083 --> 00:19.625
[gun cocks]

00:19.750 --> 00:20.958
<i>You'll see.</i>

00:22.000 --> 00:23.791
[Norm] <i>I don't think it's our job
to help these people.</i>

00:24.750 --> 00:25.708
<i>They're murderers.</i>

00:25.708 --> 00:27.375
So what do you propose we do?

00:27.375 --> 00:29.083
We can do what they would've done to us.

00:29.083 --> 00:30.500
- [crowd gasps]
- Wow.

00:30.500 --> 00:32.500
They killed my husband.

00:32.500 --> 00:35.041
<i>If your father were here, he'd...</i>

00:35.166 --> 00:36.791
he'd do the right thing.

00:36.791 --> 00:39.166
You okay?

00:39.166 --> 00:41.166
[Chet] <i>The whole
"opening the vault door for Lucy" thing</i>

00:41.166 --> 00:43.125
<i>didn't sit too well
with the council, so...</i>

00:43.125 --> 00:46.375
I guess I'm not Gate-Keeper anymore.

00:46.375 --> 00:48.500
[Lucy] <i>I need the head.</i>

00:48.500 --> 00:49.916
It's the only way
I can get my father back.

00:49.916 --> 00:51.125
[screams]

00:51.125 --> 00:53.041
<i>You can't treat people like this!</i>

00:53.041 --> 00:54.125
[growls]

00:54.125 --> 00:55.916
[Ghoul] <i>Yeah, why is that?</i>

00:55.916 --> 00:57.041
[grunts]

00:57.041 --> 00:59.416
Because of the Golden Rule.

00:59.416 --> 01:01.791
[Ghoul] <i>Wasteland's got
its own golden rule.</i>

01:01.791 --> 01:06.208
Thou shalt get sidetracked by bullshit
every goddamn time.

01:19.250 --> 01:21.333
[♪ Jack Shaindlin: "Let's Go Sunning"]

01:25.750 --> 01:27.500
<i>♪ Let's go sunning ♪</i>

01:27.500 --> 01:29.250
<i>♪ It's so good for you ♪</i>

01:29.250 --> 01:30.791
<i>♪ Let's go sunning ♪</i>

01:30.791 --> 01:32.416
<i>♪ Neath the sky of blue ♪</i>

01:32.416 --> 01:35.916
<i>♪ Greet the sun every morn ♪</i>

01:35.916 --> 01:38.583
<i>♪ Feel as free and happy
as the day you were born ♪</i>

01:38.583 --> 01:40.500
- [Ghoul coughing]
- <i>♪ Let's go native ♪</i>

01:40.500 --> 01:42.375
<i>♪ Sun your cares away ♪</i>

01:42.375 --> 01:44.291
<i>♪ Be creative ♪</i>

01:44.291 --> 01:46.083
<i>♪ Learn to live and play ♪</i>

01:46.083 --> 01:49.375
<i>♪ Pretty flowers need the sun ♪</i>

01:49.375 --> 01:52.333
<i>♪ This applies to everyone ♪</i>

01:52.333 --> 01:55.541
<i>♪ Life's worth living ♪</i>

01:55.541 --> 01:59.250
<i>♪ When nature's giving ♪</i>

01:59.250 --> 02:02.208
- <i>♪ Happiness to everyone ♪</i>
- [Roger] Roger!

02:02.208 --> 02:05.916
- My name is Roger!
- <i>♪ So let's go sunning ♪</i>

02:10.000 --> 02:12.000
[Roger snarling]

02:14.583 --> 02:16.500
[Lucy panting]

02:16.500 --> 02:18.583
[Roger snarling]

02:19.791 --> 02:23.041
[Roger] My name is Roger.

02:23.041 --> 02:25.250
[tense music playing]

02:25.250 --> 02:27.083
My name is Roger.

02:31.208 --> 02:33.208
[snarling]

02:42.208 --> 02:43.750
Roger.

02:45.583 --> 02:49.000
[yelping]

02:49.000 --> 02:52.166
Roger. My name is Roger.

02:52.166 --> 02:53.541
My name is Roger.

02:53.541 --> 02:55.958
My name's Roger.

02:55.958 --> 02:58.875
[grunting]

02:58.875 --> 03:00.833
My name is Roger.

03:00.833 --> 03:02.500
[Ghoul] Hey, Rog.

03:02.500 --> 03:05.500
[laughing] Hey. Hey.

03:07.833 --> 03:09.625
Fancy seeing you out here.

03:11.000 --> 03:13.583
You out for that bounty, too, huh?

03:13.583 --> 03:15.166
Yep.

03:17.375 --> 03:18.375
[snarling]

03:18.375 --> 03:20.625
[wailing]

03:23.500 --> 03:26.083
Oh, shit.

03:27.583 --> 03:29.875
- How you feeling?
- Oh...

03:29.875 --> 03:31.500
[chuckles]

03:31.500 --> 03:33.500
[exhales]

03:33.500 --> 03:39.125
You know... it's hard out here.

03:39.125 --> 03:41.875
Dang smoothies can be so unkind.

03:41.875 --> 03:43.916
[panting]

03:43.916 --> 03:46.125
I see you got a smoothie of your own.

03:46.125 --> 03:48.875
[snarling]

03:52.375 --> 03:54.375
- You're turning.
- [grunts]

03:54.375 --> 03:57.333
Yeah. Yeah, maybe.

03:57.333 --> 03:59.416
Maybe. [chuckles]

03:59.416 --> 04:03.416
Hey, you-you don't happen
to have any vials, do you?

04:03.416 --> 04:05.666
[sniffles]

04:05.666 --> 04:09.625
Just one little puff
and I'll be back on my feet.

04:09.625 --> 04:11.708
You know I'm good for it.

04:12.791 --> 04:14.916
I'm sorry, Roger. I'm all out.

04:14.916 --> 04:17.708
That's okay. That's okay.

04:17.708 --> 04:22.666
Though, um, you and your
smooth-faced friend, you, um...

04:22.666 --> 04:27.541
might want to clear out...
before things get ugly.

04:27.541 --> 04:29.041
[snarls]

04:31.416 --> 04:33.416
I did okay.

04:35.625 --> 04:37.750
Twenty-eight years
since I first started showing.

04:37.750 --> 04:40.541
[yelling]

04:44.000 --> 04:46.041
Oh, hell.

04:46.041 --> 04:48.041
[grunting]

04:48.041 --> 04:49.708
Not as long as you, though.

04:49.708 --> 04:52.250
You've outlasted us all.

04:52.250 --> 04:55.125
How long since
you first started wastelanding?

04:55.125 --> 04:57.458
A long time.

04:58.500 --> 05:00.083
That's a lot of vials.

05:00.083 --> 05:02.583
[Ghoul] Well, I've always been good

05:02.583 --> 05:04.166
at making money, Roger.

05:05.625 --> 05:07.458
[exhales]

05:07.458 --> 05:09.250
Say...

05:10.833 --> 05:13.000
...you remember how good
food used to taste?

05:14.500 --> 05:17.416
Yeah. BlamCo Mac & Cheese.

05:17.416 --> 05:20.416
- Ice cream and apple pie.
- [laughs]

05:20.416 --> 05:22.791
Hot damn.

05:22.791 --> 05:24.583
Apple pie.

05:24.583 --> 05:26.458
You know, my mom used to...

05:36.000 --> 05:37.416
[holsters gun]

05:41.958 --> 05:43.750
[Lucy] Wait...

05:43.750 --> 05:45.083
Why'd you do that?

05:46.125 --> 05:47.625
He was sick.

05:52.916 --> 05:54.875
[grunting]

05:54.875 --> 05:55.958
[crunch]

05:55.958 --> 05:58.166
Stop. Stop, stop. Please, I...

05:58.166 --> 06:00.750
No, I know it's hard up here,
but you don't... you don't have...

06:00.750 --> 06:04.458
you don't have to resort to... to...

06:04.458 --> 06:07.083
What'd you say your name was?

06:07.083 --> 06:09.166
Lucy MacLean.

06:09.166 --> 06:11.166
[suspenseful music playing]

06:11.166 --> 06:12.875
MacLean?

06:14.916 --> 06:16.708
Huh.

06:17.875 --> 06:20.750
- [squishing]
- Well, Lucy MacLean,

06:20.750 --> 06:25.208
it ain't all canned peaches and marmalade
left up here, sweetheart.

06:25.208 --> 06:29.041
Sometimes a fella's got to eat a fella.

06:31.041 --> 06:33.083
Mmm. Mmm.

06:34.125 --> 06:35.541
Mmm.

06:37.750 --> 06:39.916
You know, my vault
has endured hardship, too.

06:39.916 --> 06:42.291
In the Great Plague of '77,

06:42.291 --> 06:45.041
everyone had to quarantine,
they couldn't work the farms together.

06:45.041 --> 06:47.291
People starved.

06:47.291 --> 06:49.125
My mother included.

06:49.125 --> 06:51.166
My dad dropped to 128 pounds,

06:51.166 --> 06:53.500
and he still refused
to do anything like this.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.541
[laughs]

06:55.541 --> 06:57.291
What? What's so funny?

06:57.291 --> 07:01.833
Well, there's what people say they did

07:01.833 --> 07:04.250
and what they really did.

07:04.250 --> 07:08.583
I'll bet your daddy
was first in line at the cookout.

07:08.583 --> 07:15.375
I bet he had a bib with a drawing
of his neighbor's ass on there.

07:17.041 --> 07:19.375
How do you live like this?

07:20.458 --> 07:22.500
Why keep going?

07:24.750 --> 07:27.541
[dark music playing]

07:33.083 --> 07:37.041
Well, one good question deserves another.

07:39.458 --> 07:43.625
Why the fuck am I doing all the work?

07:45.208 --> 07:47.125
Now come on, Vaultie.

07:47.125 --> 07:50.166
Ass jerky don't make itself.

07:53.333 --> 07:56.958
<i>[vocalist yodeling]</i>

08:02.541 --> 08:04.541
[tense music playing]

08:20.916 --> 08:22.583
- [♪ Michael Brown: "Just Fine"]
- <i>♪ Hello, ladies, how are you? ♪</i>

08:22.583 --> 08:24.416
<i>♪ Just fine, just fine ♪</i>

08:24.416 --> 08:27.625
- <i>♪ Hello, fellas, how are you? ♪</i>
- <i>♪ Just fine ♪</i>

08:27.625 --> 08:30.875
<i>♪ It's real fine weather
when we all can get together ♪</i>

08:30.875 --> 08:34.666
- [Reg whistling]
- <i>♪ And we're all just fine, just fine ♪</i>

08:34.791 --> 08:36.541
<i>♪ Are you glad that you are here...</i>

08:36.541 --> 08:39.083
- Morning, Woody.
- Morning, Reg.

08:39.083 --> 08:41.833
- Nice work on your posters.
- Oh, thanks, Reg.

08:41.833 --> 08:45.125
I've been admiring yours as well.

08:45.125 --> 08:46.583
- Any luck?
- [snoring]

08:46.583 --> 08:48.125
I asked him all sorts of questions.

08:48.125 --> 08:50.791
Who he is, who he works for,

08:50.791 --> 08:54.000
why his colleagues kidnapped
Overseer MacLean.

08:54.000 --> 08:58.000
What organizing principle, if any,
they operate under.

08:58.000 --> 08:59.458
Nothing, huh?

09:00.958 --> 09:02.500
[exhales]

09:02.500 --> 09:05.500
[Reg] Two hundred years with no contact.

09:07.000 --> 09:09.416
The terrible things this creature
must have been through.

09:10.458 --> 09:12.291
- [shouts]
- What's he doing?

09:12.291 --> 09:14.416
[Woody] Oh, no.

09:14.416 --> 09:16.958
Sir? Please stop.
You will injure yourself.

09:16.958 --> 09:18.250
Fuck you!

09:19.416 --> 09:21.500
We better tranq him again.

09:21.500 --> 09:25.041
- For his own safety.
- We'll try again tomorrow.

09:25.041 --> 09:28.041
♪ ♪

09:41.291 --> 09:42.416
There you are.

09:42.416 --> 09:45.083
Thought you might be up here.

09:45.083 --> 09:48.250
Made pie if you'd like a piece.

09:49.750 --> 09:54.916
I was there the first time that you tried
rhubarb pie and ice cream.

09:54.916 --> 09:57.416
You sure did like pie that day.

10:01.458 --> 10:04.750
You came here to talk to me
about what I said at the assembly.

10:04.750 --> 10:07.541
And why do you think that is?

10:07.541 --> 10:09.333
It upset people.

10:09.333 --> 10:11.791
You don't like it when people get upset.

10:11.791 --> 10:13.958
But you do?

10:16.083 --> 10:20.458
You're not the only one that feels
the absence of your father.

10:20.458 --> 10:22.625
People here are hurting.

10:22.625 --> 10:25.166
Disoriented.

10:25.166 --> 10:29.333
And with your sister gone,
you're the last standing MacLean.

10:29.333 --> 10:33.666
Your voice carries more weight
than you might realize.

10:35.500 --> 10:37.000
I hid.

10:38.791 --> 10:41.458
During the raid,
I got in a storage space and I hid.

10:41.458 --> 10:43.291
[dramatic music playing]

10:43.291 --> 10:45.500
Does that make you angry?

10:47.875 --> 10:49.541
Why does it matter?

10:54.125 --> 10:56.250
Regular boys...

10:57.416 --> 11:02.041
...can get angry
and they'll just pee on the wall.

11:02.041 --> 11:04.583
When clever boys like you are angry...

11:04.583 --> 11:06.083
Hmm.

11:06.083 --> 11:09.291
You're lucky not to have seen
where that can lead.

11:16.291 --> 11:18.708
Just tread lightly.

11:21.208 --> 11:23.500
That's all I ask.

11:31.458 --> 11:33.458
[Ghoul coughing]

11:38.041 --> 11:40.041
<i>[vocalist yodeling]</i>

11:41.291 --> 11:43.291
[panting]

11:48.625 --> 11:51.083
[rad meter peaking]

11:59.958 --> 12:01.958
[Ghoul clears throat]

12:06.500 --> 12:07.916
Mmm.

12:12.000 --> 12:14.750
[dramatic music playing]

12:22.458 --> 12:24.791
[peaking intensifies]

12:25.791 --> 12:27.791
[pants]

12:28.791 --> 12:30.875
Now you're getting it.

12:30.875 --> 12:32.916
[gulping]

12:38.208 --> 12:42.708
How does that Golden Rule jibe with what's
going through your head right now?

12:51.916 --> 12:54.833
What are you?

12:55.875 --> 13:01.041
Oh, I'm you, sweetie.
You just give it a little time.

13:04.625 --> 13:06.625
[labored coughing]

13:18.291 --> 13:20.458
[tense music playing]

13:20.458 --> 13:22.166
[Lucy grunting]

13:30.708 --> 13:33.500
[jarring music playing]

13:35.458 --> 13:37.875
[groaning]

13:37.875 --> 13:39.916
[grunting]

13:42.583 --> 13:46.125
Where you think you going?
You ain't going nowhere.

13:54.041 --> 13:57.916
There you are, you little killer.

13:59.666 --> 14:01.250
Aah!

14:06.458 --> 14:08.083
[screams]

14:09.875 --> 14:11.833
[panting]

14:14.750 --> 14:20.875
Now, that right there is the closest thing
we've had to an honest exchange so far.

14:27.083 --> 14:30.458
[♪ Buddy Holly: "What to Do"]

14:30.458 --> 14:35.375
<i>♪ What to do
now that she doesn't want me ♪</i>

14:36.750 --> 14:39.208
<i>♪ That's what haunts me ♪</i>

14:40.500 --> 14:42.583
<i>♪ What to do ♪</i>

14:44.958 --> 14:49.791
<i>♪ What to do to keep from being lonely ♪</i>

14:51.166 --> 14:54.041
- <i>♪ Want her only ♪</i>
- [knock at door]

14:59.500 --> 15:01.375
- Hey.
- Hey.

15:01.375 --> 15:04.583
I thought I'd just stop by
and see how you're doing.

15:04.583 --> 15:08.083
- Not great, to be honest.
- Mm.

15:09.333 --> 15:13.875
First I lost Lucy, and then
I lost my job as the Gate-Keeper.

15:13.875 --> 15:17.541
- Right.
- How are you handling the, uh...

15:19.541 --> 15:22.583
...death of the father
of your unborn baby?

15:23.750 --> 15:24.875
Same.

15:24.875 --> 15:29.083
I was actually just organizing
some of Bert's things, and,

15:29.083 --> 15:32.916
well, I thought maybe
you might want some of them?

15:32.916 --> 15:34.000
Oh.

15:35.166 --> 15:36.750
[mutters]

15:40.833 --> 15:42.458
This is all that's left of him.

15:42.458 --> 15:44.666
He was a good man, Steph.

15:45.666 --> 15:46.583
You think so?

15:46.583 --> 15:49.666
Of course. I mean, what can you say?

15:53.750 --> 15:54.958
Well...

15:56.958 --> 15:58.708
He took great care of his shoes.

15:59.833 --> 16:02.958
You know, it was one
of the few things he truly loved.

16:02.958 --> 16:05.833
Get him talking about shoe maintenance,

16:05.833 --> 16:07.041
and... [chuckles]

16:07.041 --> 16:10.416
he'd just carry on
until everyone left the room.

16:11.708 --> 16:13.625
I loved him so much.

16:14.791 --> 16:18.416
And those monsters took him away from me.

16:18.416 --> 16:20.416
Awful.

16:20.416 --> 16:22.041
Hate those guys.

16:22.041 --> 16:26.458
It would mean a lot to me
if you took Bert's shoes.

16:27.500 --> 16:29.583
Wow.

16:29.583 --> 16:33.291
Thank you, Steph. I'll...

16:33.291 --> 16:35.791
- I'll try to wear them.
- Oh, good.

16:35.791 --> 16:37.500
And this...

16:41.500 --> 16:42.541
[gasps]

16:45.333 --> 16:47.375
Oh, Bert.

16:48.458 --> 16:51.833
Bert... Bert. [crying]

16:51.833 --> 16:54.166
- Okay...
- Oh, Bert.

16:54.166 --> 16:57.125
Oh, Bert. [sobs]

16:57.125 --> 17:00.083
Oh, Bert. [kisses]

17:00.083 --> 17:02.583
Oh, Bert.

17:02.583 --> 17:04.125
Bert.

17:05.250 --> 17:06.500
Bert.

17:06.625 --> 17:09.625
[♪ The Swallows:
"It Ain't the Meat (It's the Motion)"]

17:16.500 --> 17:17.833
Oh, no, no, no.

17:17.833 --> 17:19.750
Could you just keep it on while we...?

17:19.750 --> 17:21.458
Oh, yeah, of course, I'm sorry.

17:21.458 --> 17:22.958
- What was I thinking?
- [chuckling]

17:22.958 --> 17:25.375
<i>♪ Makes your daddy want to rock ♪</i>

17:26.375 --> 17:29.000
Oh, Bert.

17:29.000 --> 17:32.250
- Yes, I am Bert.
- Yeah.

17:32.250 --> 17:34.333
[Steph panting]

17:35.916 --> 17:37.291
[Steph moans]

17:37.291 --> 17:40.416
Now, that is one wet lady.

17:40.416 --> 17:41.666
Oh. Oh, oh, oh.

17:41.666 --> 17:44.583
[gasping]

17:44.583 --> 17:46.250
[both chuckle]

17:46.250 --> 17:47.875
- Bert!
- Oh!
- <i>♪ It's the movement ♪</i>

17:47.875 --> 17:52.458
<i>♪ That gives it the sock. ♪</i>

17:54.291 --> 17:56.291
[suspenseful music playing]

18:30.666 --> 18:32.666
[Ghoul] Transaction.

18:32.666 --> 18:33.875
[attendant] <i>Yes?</i>

18:35.625 --> 18:37.875
Two-month supply of vials.

18:37.875 --> 18:40.041
Exchange one female.
Mint condition.

18:43.625 --> 18:45.208
Near mint condition.

18:45.208 --> 18:48.791
[attendant] <i>Condition grading requires
physical evaluation.</i>

18:48.791 --> 18:50.291
<i>Please send her in.</i>

18:50.291 --> 18:52.333
[lock buzzes, latch clicks]

18:56.666 --> 18:57.916
What's in there?

19:01.041 --> 19:02.500
You're about to find out.

19:04.208 --> 19:06.041
You're selling me?

19:08.458 --> 19:11.625
You got problems
out here, too, sweetheart.

19:11.625 --> 19:14.458
Best you try your luck behind that door.

19:22.958 --> 19:23.958
Go on.

19:27.750 --> 19:29.750
[dramatic music playing]

19:52.708 --> 19:55.500
[wheezing]

20:05.458 --> 20:08.458
[♪ Sam Fonteyn: "Journey into Melody"]

20:32.875 --> 20:33.791
<i>Welcome.</i>

20:33.791 --> 20:37.083
- What the fudge?
<i>- Fudge? There's no fudge here.</i>

20:37.083 --> 20:40.291
<i>Only a General Atomics International
Mark 4.</i>

20:40.291 --> 20:43.375
<i>That's what I am.
You seem to be a woman.</i>

20:44.500 --> 20:46.250
Please, sir, my name is Lucy MacLean.

20:46.250 --> 20:49.208
My dad's been taken
and I-I-I've been kidnapped.

20:49.208 --> 20:51.000
[stammers] He's right outside--

20:51.000 --> 20:52.916
<i>I say, you've lost a finger.</i>

20:52.916 --> 20:55.541
<i>Ah, that won't do at all.</i>

20:55.541 --> 20:58.583
<i>Let's get you taken care of.
Follow me.</i>

21:07.916 --> 21:09.250
Okay.

21:11.708 --> 21:12.750
<i>Apologies for the mess.</i>

21:12.750 --> 21:15.000
<i>Time flies by lately.</i>

21:15.000 --> 21:18.250
<i>Especially since my temporal sensors
went out in the Great War.</i>

21:18.250 --> 21:20.708
<i>That must have been a week ago, at least.</i>

21:21.708 --> 21:25.125
<i>Would you mind taking a seat
on that gurney in front of you?</i>

21:26.166 --> 21:28.500
<i>Now, what have we here?</i>

21:29.541 --> 21:31.458
<i>Too fat, too withered.</i>

21:31.458 --> 21:33.500
<i>Ah, this one'll do it.</i>

21:33.500 --> 21:35.500
<i>Eh, you're lucky
I don't have to use a thumb.</i>

21:35.500 --> 21:39.500
<i>Our finger inventory's in a sorry state.</i>

21:39.500 --> 21:41.875
<i>Now, if you give me your hand...</i>

21:41.875 --> 21:43.625
[Lucy panting]

21:43.625 --> 21:46.375
<i>Okay, you're going to feel a slight pinch.</i>

21:46.375 --> 21:48.083
[soft whirring]

21:49.125 --> 21:50.083
[Lucy] Thank you.

21:50.083 --> 21:52.625
<i>- I say.</i>
- I really do appreciate this.

21:52.625 --> 21:55.791
But listen, a big fish ate my head,
and I need my head to get back to my dad--

21:55.791 --> 21:56.875
<i>There now.</i>

21:56.875 --> 21:58.625
<i>That's much better, isn't it?</i>

22:01.375 --> 22:04.500
- Thank you, that...
<i>- Not a problem.</i>

22:04.500 --> 22:07.083
That feels really, really nice.

22:07.083 --> 22:10.625
<i>Now, would you prefer a dressing
of high-quality synthetic fibers,</i>

22:10.625 --> 22:15.208
<i>classic cotton,
or a comforting synthetic-cotton blend?</i>

22:15.208 --> 22:18.000
You have... real cotton?

22:18.000 --> 22:20.375
<i>Of course. Don't you?</i>

22:20.375 --> 22:22.000
[sighs softly]

22:23.416 --> 22:24.458
Thank you.

22:24.458 --> 22:29.541
You know, that...
that creature that brought me here, he...

22:29.541 --> 22:31.583
<i>You seem unhappy.</i>

22:31.583 --> 22:33.666
- He did not treat me very courteously.
<i>- Really?</i>

22:33.666 --> 22:36.041
When I pointed out that he wasn't
following the Golden Rule,

22:36.041 --> 22:38.333
he put a leash around my neck
and he made me drink from puddle water

22:38.333 --> 22:40.166
that I'm pretty sure was just
some kind of animal pee.

22:40.166 --> 22:41.458
<i>Well, that is interesting.</i>

22:41.458 --> 22:44.333
- And I thought I was here
to be a sex slave.
<i>- What?!</i>

22:44.333 --> 22:47.166
<i>No! What a disgusting idea.</i>

22:47.166 --> 22:48.458
[chuckles]

22:48.458 --> 22:50.875
<i>I'm simply going to harvest your organs.</i>

22:50.875 --> 22:52.708
Huh?

22:54.166 --> 22:55.666
[grunts softly]

23:04.125 --> 23:06.291
[guard] Dessert tray incoming.

23:08.125 --> 23:11.250
[prisoners chattering indistinctly]

23:11.250 --> 23:12.625
[prisoner] Hey, hey.

23:12.625 --> 23:15.000
[prisoner 2] You gonna take that from her?

23:15.000 --> 23:16.291
You gonna take that?

23:17.458 --> 23:18.625
Hey, Norm.

23:18.625 --> 23:20.000
Veronica.

23:23.958 --> 23:26.083
Wait, they're getting Jell-O cake?

23:27.125 --> 23:29.291
Those are my orders.

23:29.291 --> 23:30.791
[sighs]

23:30.791 --> 23:32.500
I wonder what your dad
would say about this.

23:32.500 --> 23:34.958
He'd be handing them the cake himself.

23:34.958 --> 23:37.166
Yeah. He was a saint.

23:41.666 --> 23:42.958
Do you want it?

23:42.958 --> 23:44.500
Mm-hmm.

23:44.500 --> 23:45.541
Nobody's gonna know.

23:45.541 --> 23:47.500
[chuckles] Yeah.

23:47.500 --> 23:49.625
I'm gonna put this in my fridge.

23:57.125 --> 23:58.458
What are you looking at?

23:58.458 --> 24:00.250
[door closes]

24:00.250 --> 24:03.541
A murderer in a cage

24:03.541 --> 24:06.041
paying the price for what you did to us.

24:07.041 --> 24:09.708
For what you did
to the innocent people in Vault 32.

24:09.708 --> 24:12.125
[ominous music playing]

24:12.125 --> 24:14.791
I don't know what the people
in Vault 32 were up to.

24:16.958 --> 24:20.583
But it was anything but innocent.

24:38.083 --> 24:40.416
31 and 32.

24:47.875 --> 24:49.875
[ominous music playing]

25:03.500 --> 25:06.250
[Steph groaning]

25:09.666 --> 25:11.708
Norm. Hi.

25:11.708 --> 25:14.583
[Steph screams]

25:18.125 --> 25:19.500
Feel like getting out of the house?

25:19.500 --> 25:21.333
Yes.

25:21.333 --> 25:22.583
[screams]

25:28.875 --> 25:30.875
[mysterious music playing]

25:31.875 --> 25:33.958
[Norm] <i>Maybe he was messing with me,</i>

25:33.958 --> 25:36.541
but one of the raiders told me
there was something up in 32.

25:36.541 --> 25:37.833
[Chet] Uh-huh.

25:37.833 --> 25:41.250
Well, this isn't exactly fun for me, Norm.

25:41.250 --> 25:43.125
[Norm] Then why'd you come?

25:43.125 --> 25:44.708
[Chet] To be honest, I don't know.

25:45.750 --> 25:47.625
You don't think it's because
you're still in love with my sister

25:47.625 --> 25:48.708
and being around me reminds you of her?

25:48.708 --> 25:51.000
[Chet scoffs]

25:51.000 --> 25:52.208
Hmm.

25:52.208 --> 25:53.625
[grunts]

25:56.041 --> 25:57.833
This is so wrong.

25:57.833 --> 25:59.541
Come on. [grunts]

25:59.541 --> 26:01.875
You have to see this.

26:01.875 --> 26:04.833
Wrong, wrong, wrong.

26:23.500 --> 26:26.375
♪ ♪

26:48.875 --> 26:50.125
You see?

26:50.125 --> 26:52.833
Whatever happened here
happened a long time ago.

26:58.083 --> 27:00.083
♪ ♪

27:25.166 --> 27:27.166
♪ ♪

27:40.833 --> 27:42.541
[clicking, beeping]

27:45.583 --> 27:48.791
The last bio-signal detected
was two years ago.

27:56.375 --> 27:58.375
<i>[faint, indistinct chatter on TV]</i>

28:09.250 --> 28:12.458
[TV announcer] <i>This rodent colony
is called a mouse utopia.</i>

28:12.458 --> 28:16.166
<i>Inside, the mice enjoy all the amenities--</i>

28:16.166 --> 28:20.291
<i>all the food they can eat,
all the padding they can sleep on--</i>

28:20.291 --> 28:24.625
<i>but eventually overpopulation occurs.</i>

28:24.625 --> 28:28.583
<i>The mice fight for the once bountiful
food, the once endless space.</i>

28:28.583 --> 28:32.583
<i>They eat each other
in their desperation to survive.</i>

28:57.250 --> 29:01.166
So, if they were already dead
when the raiders got here,

29:01.166 --> 29:02.833
who killed them?

29:02.833 --> 29:08.500
I mean, it looks like they strangled
each other with their hands.

29:08.500 --> 29:11.291
It just doesn't make any sense.

29:23.583 --> 29:26.333
[♪ Sam Fonteyn: "Journey into Melody"]

29:26.333 --> 29:28.541
<i>[Snip Snip whistling]</i>

29:41.125 --> 29:43.000
[Rose] <i>Lucy.</i>

29:48.291 --> 29:49.375
[Rose] <i>Lucy, sweetie,</i>

29:49.375 --> 29:51.083
what are you doing out here?

29:51.083 --> 29:53.083
♪ ♪

30:00.250 --> 30:01.541
[Martha] My name is Martha.

30:01.541 --> 30:10.125
Martha. My name is Martha. Martha.

30:10.125 --> 30:12.125
My name is Martha.

30:12.125 --> 30:14.041
Martha.

30:17.916 --> 30:19.416
[Snip Snip] <i>Pardon the interruption.</i>

30:19.416 --> 30:23.083
<i>Our latest arrival has arrived.</i>

30:23.083 --> 30:25.250
Oh, shit.

30:25.250 --> 30:27.458
What are they asking, Snip Snip?

30:27.458 --> 30:29.291
<i>Sixty vials.</i>

30:33.250 --> 30:34.541
We can do 60.

30:34.541 --> 30:36.583
<i>- Fantastic.</i>
- Oh, do her now

30:36.583 --> 30:39.208
so she's ready for the next pickup.

30:39.208 --> 30:41.833
<i>Excellent idea as always, sir.</i>

30:41.833 --> 30:43.041
Thanks, Snip Snip.

30:43.041 --> 30:44.208
<i>Do excuse me.</i>

30:44.208 --> 30:46.291
Nice robot.

30:47.291 --> 30:49.333
[Snip Snip] <i>Where are you from again?</i>

30:49.333 --> 30:50.333
[Lucy groaning]

30:50.333 --> 30:54.666
<i>Never been there myself.
Hope to go there someday soon.</i>

30:54.666 --> 30:56.708
♪ ♪

31:02.250 --> 31:04.416
<i>Here we are.
Let's get on with it, shall we?</i>

31:04.416 --> 31:06.875
<i>We don't want to keep
your associate waiting.</i>

31:06.875 --> 31:08.958
[ominous music playing]

31:10.583 --> 31:13.083
Sir, you can't do this.

31:13.083 --> 31:15.166
Please, I need my organs.

31:15.166 --> 31:16.458
<i>Now, don't be afraid.</i>

31:16.458 --> 31:19.166
<i>A little snip-snip
and it will all be over.</i>

31:21.583 --> 31:23.583
<i>Hold still now.</i>

31:25.416 --> 31:27.708
<i>This won't hurt a bit.</i>

31:35.083 --> 31:36.958
<i>Excuse me.</i>

31:44.791 --> 31:45.875
[paddles charge]

31:45.875 --> 31:48.916
[garbled, overlapping phrases]

31:55.041 --> 31:57.041
<i>There's no fudge here.</i>

32:09.416 --> 32:12.375
<i>I am ever-ready to serve...</i>

32:12.375 --> 32:14.625
<i>to serve... to serve.</i>

32:15.666 --> 32:17.666
<i>[cartoon sound effects on TV]</i>

32:18.916 --> 32:20.750
[chuckles]

32:22.291 --> 32:23.291
Hands up.

32:23.291 --> 32:26.875
Do as I say,
and Snip Snip doesn't get hurt.

32:26.875 --> 32:28.666
[man] <i>[on TV] Calling all cars.</i>

32:28.666 --> 32:30.958
It's a fucking robot.

32:30.958 --> 32:33.875
Yeah, you might as well be holding
an air conditioner hostage.

32:33.875 --> 32:36.541
[Huey] Well, an air conditioner
sounds nice, though.

32:36.541 --> 32:38.541
[Squirrel] Yeah, an air conditioner
would be a big deal.

32:38.541 --> 32:39.791
But you know what I mean.

32:39.791 --> 32:42.375
Totally. The question was,

32:42.375 --> 32:43.541
does she know what you mean?

32:43.541 --> 32:47.125
[Lucy] Yeah. I think I do.

32:47.125 --> 32:50.375
That's why I put
Abraxo Draining Fluid in his syringes.

32:50.375 --> 32:54.291
Snip Snip, tell them what Abraxo does
to the human body.

32:54.291 --> 32:56.125
<i>If you've got a c-c-clog
that's full of muck,</i>

32:56.125 --> 33:00.458
<i>trust Abraxo Draining Fluid
t-t-to get it unstuck.</i>

33:00.458 --> 33:02.708
<i>It's v-v-very poisonous.</i>

33:03.916 --> 33:06.541
Okay, you can walk out of here.

33:06.541 --> 33:08.583
Not just me.

33:08.583 --> 33:10.666
Them, too.

33:10.666 --> 33:13.625
[uplifting music playing]

33:17.833 --> 33:21.166
[ghouls snarling]

33:29.125 --> 33:30.875
Hey, thank you.

33:38.791 --> 33:40.708
I said all of them.

33:40.708 --> 33:43.666
Lady, those-those ones,
you don't understand--

33:47.208 --> 33:49.166
Whoa.

33:54.000 --> 33:56.958
[alarm blares]

34:01.166 --> 34:03.541
Don't be scared.

34:03.541 --> 34:06.125
You're free. Go.

34:08.875 --> 34:10.666
[snarling]

34:17.833 --> 34:19.625
Oh, gosh.

34:19.625 --> 34:21.791
[snarling]

34:21.791 --> 34:24.166
[intense music playing]

34:29.916 --> 34:31.541
- [shouts]
- [Snip Snip] <i>Hello there.</i>

34:34.291 --> 34:35.791
<i>Goodbye.</i>

34:51.291 --> 34:54.416
Martha. My name is Martha.

34:54.416 --> 34:57.125
[snarling]

34:57.125 --> 34:59.166
[tense music playing]

35:04.541 --> 35:06.833
Martha. My name is Martha.

35:06.833 --> 35:10.333
That's right. Your name is Martha.

35:10.333 --> 35:13.333
[snarling]

35:14.375 --> 35:17.083
No. No.

35:22.250 --> 35:25.708
[growling] Martha. My name is Martha.

35:25.708 --> 35:27.666
Please, please.

35:29.750 --> 35:31.791
Come on, I know there's someone
in there. Talk to me.

35:34.416 --> 35:35.875
Please!

35:37.250 --> 35:39.875
[panting]

35:39.875 --> 35:41.958
[somber music playing]

35:58.583 --> 36:00.916
[Snip Snip] <i>Pardon me, madam.</i>

36:00.916 --> 36:03.416
<i>Could I help you have a better day?</i>

36:03.416 --> 36:05.458
No, thank you.

36:17.291 --> 36:19.375
[dramatic music playing]

36:33.208 --> 36:34.916
Oh, geez.

36:36.708 --> 36:38.291
[grunts]

36:53.875 --> 36:56.375
[Chet] Okay.

36:56.375 --> 37:00.083
I think it's safe to say
they went bananas.

37:00.083 --> 37:03.000
This still doesn't explain
how the raiders got in.

37:15.208 --> 37:17.833
These people were crazy.

37:17.833 --> 37:19.375
If there were any survivors down here,

37:19.375 --> 37:22.291
they probably opened the door
and welcomed the raiders right in.

37:22.291 --> 37:24.333
[typing on keyboard]

37:25.875 --> 37:27.875
[suspenseful music playing]

37:34.958 --> 37:37.833
It says it was opened from the outside.

37:37.833 --> 37:39.833
No.

37:39.833 --> 37:41.500
They'd need a Pip-Boy to open the door.

37:41.500 --> 37:43.166
They had one.

37:43.166 --> 37:44.250
Whose?

37:48.833 --> 37:50.750
My mom's.

38:03.166 --> 38:05.166
[dramatic music playing]

38:10.500 --> 38:12.500
[labored breathing]

38:19.541 --> 38:24.291
You don't get these,
you turn into one of those?

38:24.291 --> 38:25.875
That how it works?

38:48.333 --> 38:50.791
I may end up looking like you...

38:52.916 --> 38:55.416
...but I'll never be like you.

39:05.916 --> 39:07.958
Golden Rule, motherfucker.

39:19.125 --> 39:21.125
[majestic music playing]

39:40.750 --> 39:45.291
- [♪ The Andrews Sisters:
"I Can Dream, Can't I?"]
- <i>♪ Dream on ♪</i>

39:45.291 --> 39:47.958
<i>♪ Dream ♪</i>

39:47.958 --> 39:50.875
<i>♪ On...</i>

39:50.875 --> 39:51.875
[grunting]

39:51.875 --> 39:55.000
<i>♪ I can see ♪</i>

39:55.000 --> 39:57.666
<i>♪ No matter how near ♪</i>

39:57.666 --> 40:00.500
<i>♪ You'll be ♪</i>

40:00.500 --> 40:04.541
<i>♪ You'll never belong ♪</i>

40:04.541 --> 40:06.708
<i>♪ To me ♪</i>

40:07.791 --> 40:09.583
[coughs]

40:09.583 --> 40:12.583
<i>♪ But I can dream, can't I? ♪</i>

40:12.583 --> 40:16.583
<i>♪ Can't I pretend that I'm locked ♪</i>

40:16.583 --> 40:18.333
<i>♪ In the bend ♪</i>

40:18.333 --> 40:21.833
<i>♪ Of your embrace? ♪</i>

40:21.833 --> 40:24.625
<i>♪ For dreams ♪</i>

40:24.625 --> 40:27.666
<i>♪ Are just like wine ♪</i>

40:27.666 --> 40:30.708
<i>♪ And I am drunk ♪</i>

40:30.708 --> 40:34.875
<i>♪ With mine ♪</i>

40:34.875 --> 40:38.791
<i>♪ I'm aware ♪</i>

40:38.791 --> 40:42.000
<i>♪ My heart is a sad affair...</i>

40:42.000 --> 40:44.500
Are you shitting me?

40:44.500 --> 40:48.541
<i>♪ There's much disillusion ♪</i>

40:48.541 --> 40:50.708
<i>♪ There ♪</i>

40:50.708 --> 40:54.375
<i>♪ But I can dream ♪</i>

40:54.375 --> 40:57.083
<i>♪ Can't I...</i>

40:57.083 --> 40:58.541
Whoo!

40:58.541 --> 41:01.958
Ah. I'd love to share
some of this with y'all, but...

41:01.958 --> 41:03.875
[grunts]

41:05.083 --> 41:07.625
...y'all weren't invited to this party.

41:07.625 --> 41:09.666
[chuckles]

41:09.666 --> 41:11.416
<i>♪ There ♪</i>

41:11.416 --> 41:15.666
<i>♪ But I can dream ♪</i>

41:15.666 --> 41:18.916
<i>♪ Can't I? ♪</i>

41:18.916 --> 41:24.000
<i>♪ Can't I adore you? ♪</i>

41:24.000 --> 41:29.458
<i>♪ Although we are oceans apart? ♪</i>

41:29.458 --> 41:34.708
<i>♪ I can't make you open your heart ♪</i>

41:34.708 --> 41:40.208
<i>♪ But I can dream ♪</i>

41:40.208 --> 41:44.875
<i>♪ Can't I? ♪</i>

41:52.000 --> 41:53.208
[grunts]

41:53.208 --> 41:55.000
[sighs]

41:55.000 --> 41:56.875
[clicks]

41:56.875 --> 41:59.208
<i>[Western-style music playing over TV]</i>

41:59.208 --> 42:00.875
<i>[gunshot]</i>

42:14.083 --> 42:16.083
<i>[man groaning over TV]</i>

42:17.916 --> 42:23.000
<i>There's an old Mexican eulogy,</i>
"Feo, fuerte y formal."

42:23.000 --> 42:26.208
<i>Means he was ugly, strong,</i>

42:26.208 --> 42:28.541
<i>and had dignity.</i>

42:28.541 --> 42:31.083
<i>- Well, Joey...
- [gun cocks over TV]</i>

42:31.083 --> 42:33.500
<i>...I'll give you
two out of three on that front.</i>

42:35.208 --> 42:36.833
<i>[gunshot]</i>

42:36.833 --> 42:39.000
<i>[grunts]</i>

42:39.000 --> 42:42.541
<i>I hope you like the taste of lead,
you commie son of a bitch.</i>

42:42.541 --> 42:45.041
<i>[triumphant music playing over TV]</i>

42:45.041 --> 42:47.333
<i>Yee-haw!</i>

42:49.083 --> 42:51.083
♪ ♪

43:21.166 --> 43:23.166
♪ ♪

43:51.041 --> 43:53.041
♪ ♪

44:06.500 --> 44:08.458
[♪ Sam Fonteyn: "Journey into Melody"]

44:37.000 --> 44:38.958
♪ ♪

45:08.000 --> 45:09.958
♪ ♪

45:37.000 --> 45:39.458
♪ ♪
